## context
- agent-store ctx prints a compact deterministic Quick Context summary without printing individual Records by default @draft
- agent-store context is a readable alias for ctx with identical behavior and output @draft

## links
- label: agent-store link <from> <rel> <to> resolves unambiguous short Record IDs, idempotently creates one directional Link, prints Linked <from-id> <rel> <to-id>, and does not duplicate the Link when repeated
  id: q59
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh link_adds_idempotently
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store unlink <from> <rel> <to> resolves unambiguous short Record IDs, removes that directional Link, prints Unlinked <from-id> <rel> <to-id>, and exits successfully without changing other Links when repeated
  id: 80k
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh unlink_removes_idempotently
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store links <ID> resolves an unambiguous short Record ID and prints outgoing Links as out <rel> <to-id> lines followed by incoming Links as in <rel> <from-id> lines, each sorted by relation and peer Record ID
  id: cav
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh links_lists_deterministically
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> treats link.out=<rel> and link.in=<rel> as direction-plus-relation Link predicates, treats link.out.<rel>=<record-id> and link.in.<rel>=<record-id> as direction-plus-relation-plus-peer Record ID Link predicates, and composes those predicates with the existing boolean Query language
  id: l7a
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh find_filters_links
  tags: [implemented]

# domain
- label: a Store is a project-local SQLite-backed database under .agent-store
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh store_is_project_local
  tags: [implemented]
- a Record is a stored item with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, a kind, and arbitrary named fields @draft
- a Field is a key-value attribute attached to a Record @draft
- a Query is a boolean expression over Record fields, typed comparisons, parentheses, and link predicates @draft
- label: a Hook is a stored automation rule with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, supported Store Event name, optional Query condition text, Bash command, and created_at timestamp
  id: u79
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_add_stores_metadata
  tags: [implemented]
- label: each successful create, set, unset, rm, link, and unlink mutation writes one Store Event with event_type equal to the mutation name, record_id set to the affected Record ID, and link/unlink using the source Record as the affected Record
  id: rc5
  command: bash tests/facts/store_events.sh mutation_events
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Hook Run persists one Hook invocation result with Hook ID, Store Event name, affected Record ID, exit status, stdout summary, stderr summary, and creation timestamp
  id: ra7
  command: CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/facts-ra7 cargo test hook_runs_persist_invocation_results
  tags: [implemented]
- a Quick Context is a bounded Store summary intended to orient an agent before it chooses specific retrieval commands @draft
- a Link is a directional typed relation from one Record to another Record @draft
- label: one Link table shape represents one-to-one, one-to-many, and many-to-many relations without per-kind schema changes
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_links_cardinality_shape
  tags: [implemented]

# persistence
- label: SQLite schema changes are applied through migrations when a Store is opened
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh migrations_apply_on_open
  tags: [implemented]
- persistence errors preserve enough context for the CLI to print actionable failures without panics @draft
- Record storage supports querying arbitrary Field values without requiring a Rust code change for each new field name @draft

## schema
- label: the initial SQLite schema stores Records, Fields, Links, Store Events, Hooks, Hook Runs, and schema migrations in separate normalized tables
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh initial_schema_tables
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the records table stores id, kind, created_at, and updated_at as first-class columns
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh records_columns
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the record_fields table stores one row per Field with raw value plus typed columns for text, number, timestamp, boolean, and null-aware comparisons
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_fields_typed_columns
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the record_links table stores from_record_id, rel, to_record_id, and created_at with a unique key over from_record_id, rel, and to_record_id
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_links_columns_unique
  tags: [implemented]
- label: deleting a Record cascades to its Fields and Links but does not delete other Records linked to it
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_delete_cascades_links
  tags: [implemented]
- label: hard deletes write a Store Event with a pre-delete Record snapshot before removing the active Record row
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh hard_delete_store_event_snapshot
  tags: [implemented]

## migrations
- schema migrations are embedded in the Rust binary and run inside transactions when a Store is opened @implemented
- label: applied migrations are recorded with version, name, checksum, and applied_at, and checksum mismatches stop the command with an actionable error
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh migration_checksum_mismatch
  tags: [implemented]

## concurrency
- SQLite connections enable foreign keys, WAL mode, and a busy timeout so multiple concurrent agent-store processes can read and write safely @implemented
- label: agent-store create and rm either commit all Store writes for the mutation or roll them back when a later write fails
  id: 0uf
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_mutations_transactional
  tags: [implemented]

# architecture
- the crate exposes a narrow persistence interface so command behavior can be tested without depending on sqlite file layout @draft

# decisions

## open
- token-efficient agent usage uses generic CRUD commands plus short aliases instead of type-specific task or calendar subcommands @draft
- the Rust SQLite crate and async model are chosen based on simple CLI correctness, migration support, and testability rather than background service throughput @draft

# hooks
- label: Hooks without Query conditions run only after a triggering Store mutation succeeds and commits, can read the committed Record through a nested agent-store command, do not run for failed mutations, and persist one Hook Run per invocation
  id: w5s
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hooks_run_after_commit
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Query conditions are evaluated with the same boolean kind-and-Field Query language as agent-store find; matching Hooks run and persist Hook Runs, while non-matching Hooks are skipped without Hook Runs
  id: mlq
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_query_filters_records
  tags: [implemented]
- label: create, set, and unset Hooks evaluate their Query against the Record after the change; rm Hooks evaluate against the pre-delete Record snapshot
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_query_uses_mutation_snapshot
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Bash commands receive the affected Record snapshot on stdin as one default-format Record line
  id: 9i8
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_stdin_receives_record_snapshot
  tags: [implemented]
- label: A matching Hook that exits non-zero persists a Hook Run with its exit status and stderr summary, then the triggering CLI reports the Hook ID, Bash command, exit status, and stderr summary to the caller
  id: hxt
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_failure_reports_details
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Matching Hooks run sequentially after the triggering mutation commits, with each Bash command started in the project root and interrupted after the default 30-second timeout
  id: 4as
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hooks_run_sequentially_from_project_root_with_timeout
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Bash commands for create, set, unset, and rm receive AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, and AGENT_STORE_KIND matching the affected Record snapshot
  id: vun
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_env_vars_for_record_events
  tags: [implemented]
- label: A Hook timeout or non-zero exit makes the triggering CLI command exit non-zero, reports that the Store mutation already committed, and leaves the committed Record and Hook Run persisted
  id: fgg
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_mutation
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook stdout and stderr capture are capped at 8192 bytes each and the cap values are documented in command help
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_output_capture_caps_and_help
  tags: [implemented]
- link and unlink Hooks evaluate their Query against the source Record and expose the relation and target Record ID through environment variables @draft
- Hook Bash commands receive AGENT_STORE_TARGET_ID for link and unlink events @draft

# context
- Quick Context output includes total Record count, counts by kind, Hook count, and the most recent Store activity timestamp when available @draft
- Quick Context output lists common Field names separately for each Record kind rather than as one global field list @draft
- Quick Context output summarizes common per-kind status values and date windows when fields such as status, due, or start exist @draft
- Quick Context output remains bounded by a documented byte limit regardless of Store size @draft
- agent-store ctx exits successfully for an initialized empty Store and prints zero counts instead of an error @draft
- Quick Context output includes Link count and relation-name counts when Links exist @draft

# query
- label: agent-store find <Query> supports boolean expressions with and, or, not, parentheses, and comparison operators =, !=, <, <=, >, and >= over Record kind and Field text values
  id: s5i
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_boolean_syntax
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> uses the same parser for one quoted query argument and multiple query arguments, so boolean, parenthesized, and range queries return identical results in both forms
  id: ly7
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_argument_parity
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> parses Field values and query literals as null, boolean, date, timestamp, number, or text, uses type-aware equality and inequality, orders only same-typed values, and treats missing Fields as non-matches
  id: t2s
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_typed_values
  tags: [implemented]

# fields
- Field values preserve their raw input and are parsed in specificity order as null, boolean, date or timestamp, number, then text @draft
- label: key= stores an empty string Field value, key=null stores a null Field value, and agent-store unset removes a Field entirely
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh field_empty_null_unset_semantics
  tags: [implemented]

# ids
- Record IDs are generated as 6-8 character random hash strings and creation retries when a generated ID already exists @draft
- Commands that accept a Record ID require an unambiguous existing short ID and report not-found errors without creating records implicitly @draft
